        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Make weekly usage parsing optional for OpenCode Go",
        "body": "OpenCode Go recently changed its dashboard response and can omit the weekly usage window. CodexBar then rejected an otherwise valid rolling window and fell back to Zen balance.\n\n## What changed\n\n- Accept rolling-only seroval and JSON payloads.\n- Preserve weekly-window absence through the snapshot model, so the menu omits the secondary row instead of inventing 0% usage.\n- Retain nested weekly-window recovery for wrapped response shapes.\n- Keep this PR scoped to parsing; the unrelated multi-workspace probe was removed from the branch.\n\n## Proof\n\n- Before the fix, two rolling-only fixtures fail on `origin/main` with `parseFailed(\"Missing usage fields.\")`.\n- `swift test --filter OpenCodeGoUsageParserTests` — 27/27 passing.\n- `make check` — passing, zero SwiftLint violations.\n- `make test` — all 43 shards passing.\n- Autoreview — clean, no accepted/actionable findings.\n\nFixtures cover both seroval and JSON dashboard shapes. No live account, browser-cookie, or Keychain probe was run.\n",
